Design an implementation plan for adding JSON-LD structured data to a Next.js 15 App Router static blog called Amytis.

## Context

The blog has no JSON-LD at all. The goal is to implement structured data for:
1. **Article/BlogPosting** - for posts and flows (daily notes)
2. **Book** - for book landing pages  
3. **BreadcrumbList** - for posts (including posts in series), book chapters

## Technical environment
- Next.js 15 App Router (Server Components)
- No new npm dependencies should be added (JSON-LD is pure data, no library needed)
- JSON-LD is injected via `<script type="application/ld+json" dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: JSON.stringify(schema) }} />` in page component return — this is the official Next.js pattern
- TypeScript

## Key data types available

```typescript
interface PostData {
  slug: string;
  title: string;
  date: string;          // ISO "YYYY-MM-DD"
  excerpt: string;
  category: string;
  tags: string[];
